"n.(峭壁的)边沿，边缘 【英】 n.(峭壁的)边沿，边 缘(the edge of a steep place; verge, border) 【记】 比较：blink(眨眼睛) ，在峭壁的边缘吓得 直眨眼睛(blink at the brink of a cliff) n. (河、海、峭壁等的)边缘; (危险或刺激性事物的)边缘 = verge = border 【例】on the brink of the grave 濒于死亡 【记】blink(v 眨眼)－在峭壁的边缘吓得直闭眼 【根】bri = brim边－悬崖 【记】同brim；音: 边；drink brink(河边)水；音：杯 + drink 杯子喝水时在边上喝 brink (n.)  early 13c., from Middle Low German brink ""edge,"" or Danish brink ""steepness, shore, bank, grassy edge,"" from Proto-Germanic *brenkon, probably from PIE *bhreng-, variant of root *bhren- ""project, edge"" (cognates: Lithuanian brinkti ""to swell"")."
